# Blog Project Rules

## Styling

- **NEVER create page-specific CSS files.** All pages must use `css/style.css`.
- **NEVER add inline styles** to HTML elements.
- When a new style is needed, add it to `css/style.css` so it can be reused.
- Edit CSS variables in `:root` to change colors, fonts, or spacing globally.
- Prefer existing CSS classes over creating new ones.

## HTML Structure

- All HTML pages must link to `../css/style.css` (or `css/style.css` from root).
- Use the template at `posts/_template.html` when creating new blog posts.
- Navigation must be consistent across all pages — when adding a category, update ALL files.

## JavaScript

- Do not use semicolons.
- Always use arrow functions.
- Keep JavaScript minimal; this is a static blog.

## Categories

The current categories are:
- Development (`categories/development.html`)
- Management (`categories/management.html`)
- Fishing (`categories/fishing.html`)
- Gaming (`categories/gaming.html`)
- Misc (`categories/misc.html`)

To add a new category:
1. Create the category page in `categories/`
2. Update the `<nav class="main-nav">` in ALL HTML files

## File Naming

- Use lowercase with hyphens for file names: `my-post-title.html`
- Category slugs: `development`, `management`, `fishing`, `gaming`, `misc`

## Content Guidelines

- Post content goes inside `<div class="post-content">`
- Use semantic HTML: `<article>`, `<header>`, `<main>`, `<footer>`
- Use `<pre><code>` for code blocks
- Use `<blockquote>` for quotes

## Shell Scripts

- Use POSIX-compliant shell only (no bashisms).
- No bash-only features like `[[`, arrays, or `source`.

